Jeanette Chabalala, News24(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Watch as several armed men stormed a businessman for a second time in Bergville, KwaZulu-Natal.WATCHDurban &ndash; A man was killed in a shooting incident in Westville in Durban on Saturday evening, KwaZulu-Natal paramedics said.Paramedics were called to the scene in Chearsley Road just after 20:00, RescueCare spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said.On arrival, the man believed to be in his 40s was in a critical condition and had sustained a single gunshot wound.Paramedics worked on the critically injured man however he went into cardiac arrest. The man was declared dead on scene.The motive for the shooting was unknown. Police were on scene for further investigations. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.